{
  "texts": [
    "We grouped similar codes together, aiming to solidify the underlying motives and rationales associated with the chatbot customization and emotional needs.In this study, we focused on qualitative insights instead of quantitative measures as we sought an in-depth, contextual, and nuanced understanding of how and why individual participants customize chatbots for emotional support in particular ways, which can be difficult to quantify with numbers.",
    "To protect participants' privacy, we anonymized all the data and used P# to denote them.",
    "Customization PracticeThroughout the study, participants engaged in 1541 conversation rounds (one round refers to one message from the participant and one reply from the chatbot).",
    "A total of 178 conversation sessions were logged (an average of 8 sessions per person), each lasting approximately 4 to 37 minutes, excluding inactive time.",
    "Participants created 118 distinctive personas, ranging from 1 to 13 personas per participant."
  ]
}